<br>
The thing about rampage hitting the MT is pretty much bunk.  People see the proc during a round of hits and assume they're being rampaged when it's just normal melee.  Just like Sscaley said.  If rampage hit the MT, the mob would be doing far greater damage to the MT than a Flurrying mob.  Don't ya think tanks would notice that kind of thing?  8-hit rounds would also kinda stand out in a log file. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=prenn>Prenn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 2<br> <font color=#FF0000>(12/31/02 8:34:11 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2589.topic&index=23>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Rampage</span><hr size=1> While my guild was learning vindi, I ended up having to tank him serveral times (being lvl60 monk made me our highest melee damage dealer usually, and back when FD was really, really broken, it was very hard to 'jolt' him, so after a warrior or two would go down I'd be up.) I'd always pop whirlwind, our version of furious, since his rate of attack is so high. When he rampaged, he would hit me through whirlwind.<br>
