<br>
Rampage list is set in stone, the ONLY reason that you'd notice that the rampage target changes is because you didn't set it properly.   If Rampage Target 1 is out of range, then it'll go to Rampage target 2, and so on.  The target is set in stone.   <br>
<br>
I'll give an example:   <br>
<br>
You're fighting IV, the puller will get on rampage list, if you do not toally and completely clear the mob's hate list with memblur until he has no target, then he's still on the rampage list.   Enchanter runs in to do CC on the sides, same thing happens.  He or she is on the list, but is far enough away that he or she isn't the rampage target, then the next or &quot;set&quot; RT is taking rampage, enchanter moves in and &quot;wtf?&quot; he's on rampage list, even higher than your dedicated RT.<br>
<br>
*if* your RT target is changing, it's because you didn't properly prepare the rampage list, and you cannot look to &quot;bugged rampage&quot; or &quot;it doesn't work that way&quot;, it ALWAYS works that way, and it works EVERY SINGLE TIME.    When properly set, there is no way to screw up rampage.   In all the time I've done rampaging mobs (From Tormax all the way up to VT and into the planes) if properly set, it has never once failed.    If it were as volatile as I've seen portrayed here, no one would ever beat Ahvi, ever.   He can be beaten in 20 seconds if you properly set up rampage, he'll destroy you if you don't, it's as simple as that. <p><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.hostmysig.com/data/fearsons/rohan2.jpg"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></div><!--EZCODE CENTER END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=throag>Throag</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 75<br> <font color=#FF0000>(3/1/03 10:44:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2589.topic&index=28>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Rampage</span><hr size=1> Rampage can hit the one that has aggro on PoP<br>
